#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "Securing DokuWiki"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:212
#, no-wrap
msgid "Besides the ACL policy that you just created, consider:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your Firewall"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Neither of these firewall examples makes any sort of assumptions about what other services you might need to allow on your Dokuwiki server. These rules are based on our testing environment and **ONLY** deal with allowing access to a LOCAL network ip block. You will need more services allowed for a production server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:220
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before you call everything done, you need to think about security. First, you should be running a firewall on the server. We will assume you are using one of the firewalls below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "Instead of everyone having access to the wiki, we are going to assume that anyone on the 10.0.0.0/8 network is on your private Local Area Network, and that those are the only people who need access to the site.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "`iptables` Firewall (deprecated)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The `iptables` firewall process here has been deprecated in Rocky Linux 9.0 (still available, but likely to disappear in future releases, perhaps as early as Rocky Linux 9.1). For this reason, we recommend skipping to the `firewalld` procedure below if you are doing this on 9.0 or better. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note that you may need other rules for other services on this server, and that this example only takes into account the web services.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, modify or create the _/etc/firewall.conf_ file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:234
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/index.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "`vi /etc/firewall.conf`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#IPTABLES=/usr/sbin/iptables\n"
"\n"
"#  Unless specified, the default for OUTPUT is ACCEPT\n"
"#  The default for FORWARD and INPUT is DROP\n"
"#\n"
"echo \"   clearing any existing rules and setting default policy..\"\n"
"iptables -F INPUT\n"
"iptables -P INPUT DROP\n"
"# web ports\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -m tcp -s 10.0.0.0/8 --dport 80 -j ACCEPT\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -m tcp -s 10.0.0.0/8 --dport 443 -j ACCEPT\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -i lo -j ACCEPT\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -m state --state ESTABLISHED,RELATED -j ACCEPT\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -j REJECT --reject-with tcp-reset\n"
"iptables -A INPUT -p udp -j REJECT --reject-with icmp-port-unreachable\n"
"\n"
"/usr/sbin/service iptables save\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the script is created, make sure it is executable:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:258
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/index.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "`chmod +x /etc/firewall.conf`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:260
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then execute the script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:262
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/index.md:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "`/etc/firewall.conf`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:264
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will execute the rules and save them so that they will be reloaded on the next start of _iptables_ or on boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:265
#, no-wrap
msgid "`firewalld` Firewall"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you are using `firewalld` as your firewall (and by this time, you probably *should* be) you can apply the same concepts using `firewalld's firewall-cmd` syntax.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:270
#, no-wrap
msgid "We will duplicate the `iptables` rules (above) with `firewalld` rules:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"firewall-cmd --zone=trusted --add-source=10.0.0.0/8 --permanent\n"
"firewall-cmd --zone=trusted --add-service=http --add-service=https --permanent\n"
"firewall-cmd --reload\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have the above rules added and the firewalld service reloaded, list out your zone to make sure that everything is there that you need:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "firewall-cmd --zone=trusted --list-all\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:284
#, no-wrap
msgid "which should show you something like this if all of the above has worked correctly:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"trusted (active)\n"
"  target: ACCEPT\n"
"  icmp-block-inversion: no\n"
"  interfaces: \n"
"  sources: 10.0.0.0/8\n"
"  services: http https\n"
"  ports: \n"
"  protocols: \n"
"  forward: yes\n"
"  masquerade: no\n"
"  forward-ports: \n"
"  source-ports: \n"
"  icmp-blocks: \n"
"  rich rules:\n"
msgstr ""

